pesticide.PPE: Long-sleeve shirt and long pants; Chemical resistant gloves: Barrier Laminate or Nitrile Rubber (≥ 14 mils) or Neoprene Rubber (≥ 14 mils) or Viton (≥ 14 mils); Shoes plus socks; Shirt, pants, socks, shoes and waterproof gloves when mixing and loading using a closed spray tank transfer system; NIOSH-approved elastomeric half mask respirator with organic vapor cartridges and combination R or P filters or NIOSH-approved gas mask with OV canisters or powered air purifying respirator with OV cartridges and combination HE filters when working in non-ventilated space; Protective eyewear when working in non-ventilated space
pesticide.trade_Name: Liquid Harvest Pro Indoor & Outdoor Insect Control

Safety_Information.general_Info: Harmful if swallowed, inhaled or absorbed through skin. Avoid contact with skin, eyes or clothing. Avoid breathing spray mist. Wash thoroughly with soap and water after handling and before eating, drinking, chewing gum, or using tobacco. Remove contaminated clothing and wash before reuse.
Safety_Information.if_In_Eyes: Hold eye open and rinse slowly and gently with water for 15-20 minutes. Remove contact lenses, if present, after the first 5 minutes, then continue rinsing. Call a poison control center or doctor for treatment advice.
Safety_Information.if_Swallowed: Call a poison control center or doctor immediately for treatment advice. Have person sip a glass of water if able to swallow. Do not induce vomiting unless told to by the poison control center or doctor. Do not give anything to an unconscious person.
Safety_Information.if_Inhaled: Move person to fresh air. If person is not breathing, call 911 or an ambulance, then give artificial respiration, preferably by mouth-to-mouth, if possible. Call a poison control center or doctor for further treatment advice.
Safety_Information.if_On_Skin: Take off contaminated clothing. Rinse skin immediately with plenty of water for 15-20 minutes. Call a poison control center or doctor for treatment advice.
Safety_Information.physician_Note: This product is a pyrethroid. If large amounts have been ingested, the stomach and intestine should be evacuated. Treatment is symptomatic and supportive. Digestible fats, oils, or alcohol may increase absorption and so should be avoided.
